 *
 * Doctrine Principle 10 — Tiered Model Isolation:
 *   Tier 0 (local): routing, identity, classification, heartbeat
 *   Tier 1 (free cloud): fallback only
 *   Tier 2 (paid cloud): user-facing responses ONLY
 *   Tier 3 (premium): break-glass escalation
 *
 * Primary roles:
 *   chat          — conversational, fast (Colloquium/Symposium are NOT here — see squidley-voice.ts)
 *   code          — code generation and review
 *   agent         — structured JSON output, multi-step reasoning
 *   classify      — lightweight task classification (Brain Map) — LOCAL ONLY
 *   vision        — image/document extraction (Archivum cloud path)
 *   reason        — deep reasoning, security review
 *   grimoire      — intent -> shell plan translation
 *   codex         — iterative code agent loop
 *
 * Extended roles:
 *   fallback-chat  — chat failover when primary fails
 *   fallback-code  — code failover when primary fails
 *   agent-planner  — high-level agent planning and task decomposition
